title.narrative: COMMUNITY CAPACITY FOR HIGH-IMPACT ANDINTEGRATED INTERVENTIONS

description.narrative: By 2022, the community platforms are equipped to provide high-impact interventions of integrated health / HIV, nutrition and quality Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) services., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Climate Change, Disaster Risks And Envionmental Degradation, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Disaster Risk Reduction, Early Childhood Development, Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Environmental Sustainability, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition In Early Childhood (Covid), Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Sanitation, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid), Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Water, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022,boys and girls aged 0-59 months, adolescents and women (especially those living in the most disadvantaged communities) have access to basic services, use packages of multisectoral high-impact, gender-sensitive interventions (health /HIV, nutrition, WASH) and adopt appropriate behaviours.
